{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"OUDSThemesInverse"}],"role":"collection","title":"OUDSThemesInverse","roleHeading":"Framework","externalID":"OUDSThemesInverse","symbolKind":"module"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"text":"This theme overrides the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Orange theme"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" for some colors so as to bring an “inverse”-colored experience.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is an override of the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudsthemesorange\/","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" with some inverted colors. It can override any properties from its superclass. We did not plan to make ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse\/InverseTheme","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" derivable.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The aim of the theme is to provide a particular set of colors for dedicated applications and use cases, like for example B2B apps or teams needing eye comfort. It can be seen as an extended dark mode."}]},{"text":"How to use the theme","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"How-to-use-the-theme"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse\/InverseTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" directly. You will have to use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSThemeableView"},{"type":"text","text":" for your root view and give it an instance of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse\/InverseTheme"},{"type":"text","text":". Keep in mind the themes are "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift class objects"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and can be heavy, so you may use only as instance as singleton and not store any properties."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import OUDS \/\/ To get OUDSThemeableView","import OUDSThemeInverse \/\/ To get Inverseheme","import SwiftUI","","@main","struct YourApp: App {","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            OUDSThemeableView(theme: InverseTheme()) {","                \/\/ Your root view","            }","        }","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then, in your views, you can simply use the theme through an environment variable to get the tokens:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import OUDS \/\/ To get the theme environment variable","import SwiftUI","","struct SomeView: View {","","    \/\/ Get OUDS environment variable for theme thanks to themeable view","    @Environment(\\.theme) var theme","    ","    var body: some View {","        ","        \/\/ Use the theme to retrieve the tokens","        \/\/ For spaces: theme.spaces","        \/\/ For sizes: theme.sizes","        \/\/ For borders: theme.borders","        \/\/ For elevations: theme.elevations","        \/\/ For opacities: theme.opacities","        \/\/ For colors: theme.colors","    }","}",""]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudsthemesinverse"]}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse\/InverseTheme"],"title":"Group","anchor":"Group"}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"references":{"doc://OUDSThemesInverse/documentation/OUDSThemesInverse":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse","type":"topic","title":"OUDSThemesInverse","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This theme overrides the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Orange theme"}]},{"type":"text","text":" for some colors so as to bring an “inverse”-colored experience."}],"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/oudsthemesinverse"},"doc://OUDSThemesInverse/documentation/OUDSThemesInverse/InverseTheme":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesInverse\/InverseTheme","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"InverseTheme","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This is an override of the default basic "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OrangeTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" with some inverted colors."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It can overrides any properties from its superclass, but is not derivable."}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"InverseTheme","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/oudsthemesinverse\/inversetheme","type":"topic","title":"InverseTheme"},"https://ios.unified-design-system.orange.com/documentation/oudsthemesorange/":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Orange theme"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudsthemesorange\/","url":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudsthemesorange\/","type":"link","title":"Orange theme"}}}